Comments: F11 is a mutant strain of Rhodospirillum rubrum (ATCC 11170) with approximately 75 genomic nucleotide differences with the previously published wild type genome. The mutant phenotype is of interest as it cannot survive anaerobically, while the wild type strain can. This is relevant to the biosynthesis of rhodoquinone, a cofactor required for anaerobic growth and the malate dismutation pathway. F11 does not produce rhodoquinone due to one of these mutations.

Comments: Collection of 3,087 bacterial metagenome-assembled genomes (MAGs) recovered from metagenomes available from the Sequence Read Archive. Comments: Rhodospirillum rubrum is a Gram-negative, pink-coloured facultative anaerobe capable of producing polyhydroxyalkanoates (bioplastics) from various substrates. Here, we present the complete genome of the type strain DSM 467, obtained from DSMZ collection.

Comments: A collection of draft assemblies of single bacteria isolated in silico from metagenomic sequences of human stool samples.;derived from metagenome

Challenges in cultivating microorganisms have limited the phylogenetic diversity of currently available microbial genomes. This is being addressed by advances in sequencing throughput and computational techniques that allow for the cultivation-independent recovery of high-quality bacterial and archaeal genomes directly from metagenomic data. In this study, we recovered 7,903 uncultivated genomes from >1,000 metagenomes available from the Sequence Read Archive. These genomes increase the phylogenetic diversity of current archaeal and bacterial genome trees by >30%.;derived from metagenome

Rhodospirillum rubrum ATCC 11170. This bacterium can grow using carbon monoxide as the sole carbon and energy source and the cells contain a well characterized nitrogenase system that is post-translationally modified by ADP-ribosylation.
